description:
Despite writing much on child rearing, Ellen White's son Edson White would grow up to be a 'problem' child and would often lie and be deceitful. However, when he was 44, he accepted Jesus as his saviour and converted to Adventism. He would then go on to do a remarkable work, predominantly in the South.

To find out more information about Edson White, please visit our website to read our extended article.
https://lineagejourney.com/read/edson-white-his-conversion-and-work
